cs.CV, cs.CL, cs.AI, cs.LG, cs.IR 

This paper deals with the task of textual grounding, which involves linking natural language descriptions to specific regions in an image. This task is relevant to computer vision (cs.CV), natural language processing (cs.CL), and artificial intelligence (cs.AI). The paper proposes a new algorithm that is able to consider significantly more proposals and doesn't rely on a successful first stage hypothesizing bounding box proposals, which involves optimization techniques (cs.LG) and information retrieval (cs.IR). Therefore, the most likely categories are cs.CV, cs.CL, cs.AI, cs.LG, and cs.IR.
